<section class="overview">
  <h2>How You Can Help</h2>

  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h3>Adult Leader Opportunities</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>High Adventure Committee Chair:</strong> Overall program leadership</li>
      <li><strong>Trek Advisor:</strong> 2–4 adults per crew supporting youth leaders</li>
      <li><strong>Chaperone:</strong> Travel with group, support logistics</li>
      <li><strong>Food/Meal Planner:</strong> Coordinate menus and shopping</li>
      <li><strong>Gear Coordinator:</strong> Help source and organize equipment</li>
      <li><strong>Medical Support:</strong> First Aid/CPR trained adults needed</li>
      <li><strong>Driver:</strong> Help with gear shuttles and transport</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="overview">
  <h2>Participation Requirements</h2>

  <h3>Before the Trip</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Complete annual health form (Parts A, B, C)</li>
    <li>Provide complete medication list</li>
    <li>Disclose any health concerns</li>
    <li>Ensure prescriptions are properly labeled</li>
    <li>Update emergency contact information</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Physical Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Swim classification for water-based programs</li>
    <li>Backpacking experience for Philmont</li>
    <li>Strong swimming for Northern Tier</li>
    <li>Moderate fitness for all programs</li>
  </ul>
</section>

